 Disabled American Veterans Logo
The Disabled American Veterans is an organization created in 1920 by World War I veterans for disabled military veterans of the United States Armed Forces that helps them and their families through various means. It was issued a federal charter by Congress in 1932. It currently has over 1 million members. As a 501 social welfare organization, it is outside the purview of – and therefore not rated by – Charity Navigator.
You can download theDAVlogo on full-version of the page.

Wounded Warrior Project Logo
Wounded Warrior Project is a charity and veterans service organization that offers a variety of programs, services and events for wounded veterans of the military actions following September 11, 2001. It operates as a nonprofit 501 organization. As of August 22, 2021, WWP served 157,975, registered alumni and 40,520 registered family support members. The organization has partnered with several other charities, including the American Red Cross, Resounding Joy, a music therapy group in California, and Operation Homefront.
You can download theWounded Warrior Projectlogo on full-version of the page.
